init_oa_search_lib(25.10)                            init_oa_search_lib(25.10)

Name
       init_oa_search_lib

Syntax
        init_oa_search_lib <list_of_OA_ref_libs>

       Type: String

       Default: *

       Specifies  the  list  of  OpenAccess reference libraries to be searched
       when cells are used in the Verilog netlist that are not included in the
       list of cells in the libraries specified in  init_oa_ref_lib  list.  By
       default  all  libraries  in  the  cds.lib  are  searched.  The init_ab-
       stract_view and init_layout_view lists are used to indicate which  view
       names  are looked for during the search. Applies only when init_verilog
       is used to specify the connectivity to be read. Used by the init_design
       command.

Related Information
              * init_abstract_view

              * init_design

              * init_layout_view

              * init_verilog

